==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coinsurance
<hw>Co`in*sur"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Co-</ets>
+ <ets>insurance</ets>.]</ety> <def>Insurance jointly with another or
others; specif., that system of fire insurance in which the insurer is
treated as insuring himself to the extent of that part of the risk not
covered by his policy, so that any loss is apportioned between him and
the insurance company on the principle of average, as in marine
insurance or between other insurers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cointense</ent>⟦br⟧
